.TH LSPORT 1 "January 2026" "lsport 0.3.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lsport \- TUI and CLI tool for managing local and remote ports via SSH
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lsport
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B lsport describe
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIPORT_OR_PID\fR
.br
.B lsport kill
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fB\-\-pid\fR \fIPID\fR | \fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lsport
is a fast, interactive terminal user interface (TUI) and command-line tool
for managing ports on local and remote machines via SSH. It allows you to
quickly identify which process is using a port and kill it with a single keystroke.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \(bu 4
Live port monitoring with real-time updates
.IP \(bu 4
TCP and UDP support with multiple detection methods
.IP \(bu 4
Remote server monitoring via SSH
.IP \(bu 4
CLI mode with describe and kill commands
.IP \(bu 4
Vim-style navigation with keyboard shortcuts
.IP \(bu 4
Process termination with a single keystroke
.IP \(bu 4
Regex filtering for ports, PIDs, and process names
.IP \(bu 4
Zombie process detection with visual highlighting
.IP \(bu 4
K9s-inspired dark theme UI with color-coded information
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Remote host to monitor. Format: \fIuser@host:port\fR or \fIuser@host\fR or \fIhost\fR.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-identity " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to SSH private key. If not specified, uses ssh-agent or default keys
(~/.ssh/id_ed25519, ~/.ssh/id_rsa, ~/.ssh/id_ecdsa).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-scan\-interval " " \fISECS\fR
Scan interval in seconds. Default is 2.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH CLI COMMANDS
.TP
.B describe \fIPORT_OR_PID\fR
Get detailed information about a port or process by port number or PID.
Output includes port number, protocol, PID, process name, CPU usage,
memory usage, parent process status, and zombie process detection.
.TP
.B kill
Kill a process by PID or port number. Requires either \fB\-\-pid\fR or
\fB\-\-port\fR to be specified.
.SS Describe Command Options
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Remote host to query. Format: \fIuser@host:port\fR or \fIuser@host\fR or \fIhost\fR.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-identity " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to SSH private key. If not specified, uses ssh-agent or default keys.
.SS Kill Command Options
.TP
.BR \-\-pid " " \fIPID\fR
Kill process by PID.
.TP
.BR \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Kill process by port number.
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Remote host to query. Format: \fIuser@host:port\fR or \fIuser@host\fR or \fIhost\fR.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-identity " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to SSH private key. If not specified, uses ssh-agent or default keys.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force kill using SIGKILL instead of SIGTERM.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR \(ua " / " k
Move selection up.
.TP
.BR \(da " / " j
Move selection down.
.TP
.B PgUp
Move up 10 rows.
.TP
.B PgDn
Move down 10 rows.
.TP
.B Home
Go to first entry.
.TP
.B End
Go to last entry.
.SS Actions
.TP
.B Enter
Kill selected process.
.TP
.B /
Enter filter mode (supports regex).
.TP
.B ?
Toggle help popup.
.TP
.B Esc
Clear filter or close help.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SS Sorting (K9s-style)
.TP
.BR Shift+P " / " 1
Sort by Port.
.TP
.BR Shift+O " / " 2
Sort by Protocol.
.TP
.BR Shift+I " / " 3
Sort by PID.
.TP
.BR Shift+N " / " 4
Sort by Name.
.TP
.BR Shift+C " / " 5
Sort by CPU %.
.TP
.BR Shift+M " / " 6
Sort by Memory.
.PP
Press the same key again to toggle ascending/descending order.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Monitor localhost:
.B lsport
.TP
Monitor with sudo (needed for killing system processes):
.B sudo lsport
.TP
Monitor a remote server via SSH:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com
.TP
Remote server with custom SSH port:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com:2222
.TP
Use a specific SSH key:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com \-i ~/.ssh/my_key
.TP
Custom scan interval (5 seconds):
.B lsport \-s 5
.TP
Describe a port:
.B lsport describe 8080
.TP
Describe a PID:
.B lsport describe 12345
.TP
Describe on remote server:
.B lsport describe \-H user@example.com 8080
.TP
Kill process by port:
.B lsport kill \-\-port 8080
.TP
Kill process by PID:
.B lsport kill \-\-pid 12345
.TP
Force kill a process:
.B lsport kill \-\-port 8080 \-\-force
.TP
Kill on remote server:
.B lsport kill \-\-port 8080 \-H user@example.com
.SH SSH AUTHENTICATION
For remote monitoring, authentication is attempted in this order:
.IP 1. 4
Specified key (\fB\-i\fR flag)
.IP 2. 4
SSH agent (if running)
.IP 3. 4
Default keys: ~/.ssh/id_ed25519, ~/.ssh/id_rsa, ~/.ssh/id_ecdsa
.SH FILTERING
Press \fB/\fR to enter filter mode. Filters support:
.IP \(bu 4
Simple text: \fBnode\fR matches any entry containing "node"
.IP \(bu 4
Regex patterns: \fB^80[0-9]{2}$\fR matches ports 8000-8099
.IP \(bu 4
All filters are case-insensitive
